<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,2012,2039]" lastBlockId="4.[151,1437,151,465]" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="83" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,350,2012,2039]" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">Taxonomic note:</emphasis>
The genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Moore, 1878" authorityName="Moore" authorityYear="1878" box="[480,725,2012,2039]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Nishada" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="82" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[480,573,2012,2038]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">Nishada</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Moore, F." box="[580,725,2013,2039]" pageId="3" pageNumber="82" pagination="3 - 36" refId="ref9954" refString="Moore, F. (1878) A revision of certain genera of European and Asiatic Lithosiidae, with characters of new Genera and Species. Proceedings of the Zoological Society of London, 1878, 3 - 36, 3 pls. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1469 - 7998.1878. tb 07927. x" type="journal article" year="1878">Moore, 1878</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
was erected as monotypic for its 
<typeStatus box="[1101,1149,2013,2039]" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">type</typeStatus>
species, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Moore" authorityYear="1878" box="[1252,1391,2012,2038]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Nishada" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="82" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flabrifera">
<emphasis box="[1252,1391,2012,2038]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">N. flabrifera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
under the subfamily 
<taxonomicName box="[352,478,151,177]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Lithosiinae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="83" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Lithosiidae">Lithosiinae</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName box="[492,622,151,177]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Lithosiinae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="83" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Lithosiidae">Lithosiidae</taxonomicName>
) (currently recognised as tribe 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Billberg" authorityYear="1820" box="[966,1077,151,177]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="83" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Lithosiini">Lithosiini</taxonomicName>
) from Calcutta [Kolkata], 
<collectingCountry box="[1372,1433,151,177]" name="India" pageId="4" pageNumber="83">India</collectingCountry>
. Presently, the genus represents 20 species (including the nominotypical subspecies) and one subspecies distributed mainly in the Indo-Australian tropics and rarely in the higher latitudes, such as in 
<collectingCountry box="[1080,1147,223,249]" name="Nepal" pageId="4" pageNumber="83">Nepal</collectingCountry>
and North-eastern Himalaya of the Palaearctic zone (
<bibRefCitation author="Holloway, J. D." box="[480,659,259,285]" pageId="4" pageNumber="83" refId="ref9429" refString="Holloway, J. D. (2001) The Moths of Borneo: Part 7; Family Arctiidae: Lithosiinae. Malayan Nature Journal, Southdene Sdn Bhd., 297 pp., 8 pls." type="book" year="2001">Holloway 2001</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Joshi, R. &amp; Kirti, J. S. &amp; Singh, N." box="[671,863,259,285]" pageId="4" pageNumber="83" pagination="128 - 132" refId="ref9547" refString="Joshi, R., Kirti, J. S. &amp; Singh, N. (2016) A new species of genus Nishada Moore, 1878 (Lepidoptera, Erebidae, Arctiinae) from India. Zootaxa, 4179 (1), 128 - 132. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4179.1.10" type="journal article" year="2016">
Joshi 
<emphasis box="[737,795,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="83">et al.</emphasis>
2016
</bibRefCitation>
). Of which, four species are known from 
<collectingCountry box="[1338,1398,259,285]" name="India" pageId="4" pageNumber="83">India</collectingCountry>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Holloway, 2001" authorityName="Holloway" authorityYear="2001" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Nishada" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="83" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="chilomorpha" subSpecies="adunca">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="83">N. chilomorpha adunca</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Holloway, J. D." box="[391,572,295,321]" pageId="4" pageNumber="83" refId="ref9429" refString="Holloway, J. D. (2001) The Moths of Borneo: Part 7; Family Arctiidae: Lithosiinae. Malayan Nature Journal, Southdene Sdn Bhd., 297 pp., 8 pls." type="book" year="2001">Holloway, 2001</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Moore, 1878" authorityName="Moore" authorityYear="1878" box="[583,877,295,321]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Nishada" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="83" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flabrifera">
<emphasis box="[583,723,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="83">N. flabrifera</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Moore, F." box="[730,877,295,321]" pageId="4" pageNumber="83" pagination="3 - 36" refId="ref9954" refString="Moore, F. (1878) A revision of certain genera of European and Asiatic Lithosiidae, with characters of new Genera and Species. Proceedings of the Zoological Society of London, 1878, 3 - 36, 3 pls. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1469 - 7998.1878. tb 07927. x" type="journal article" year="1878">Moore, 1878</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Joshi &amp; N. Singh" authorityName="Joshi &amp; N. Singh" box="[888,1343,295,321]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Nishada" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="83" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pseudochilomorpha">
<emphasis box="[888,1143,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="83">N. pseudochilomorpha</emphasis>
Joshi &amp; N. Singh
</taxonomicName>
in 
<bibRefCitation author="Joshi, R. &amp; Kirti, J. S. &amp; Singh, N." pageId="4" pageNumber="83" pagination="128 - 132" refId="ref9547" refString="Joshi, R., Kirti, J. S. &amp; Singh, N. (2016) A new species of genus Nishada Moore, 1878 (Lepidoptera, Erebidae, Arctiinae) from India. Zootaxa, 4179 (1), 128 - 132. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4179.1.10" type="journal article" year="2016">
Joshi 
<emphasis box="[151,208,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="83">et al.</emphasis>
, 2016
</bibRefCitation>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Walker, 1862" authorityName="Walker" authorityYear="1862" box="[332,676,331,357]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Nishada" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="83" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rotundipennis">
<emphasis box="[332,520,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="83">N. rotundipennis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Walker, F." box="[527,676,331,357]" pageId="4" pageNumber="83" pagination="82 - 145" refId="ref11439" refString="Walker, F. (1862) Catalogue of the Heterocerous Lepidopterous Insects collected at Sarawak, in Borneo, by Mr. A. R. Wallace, with Descriptions of New Species. Journal and Proceedings of the Linnean Society, Zoology, 6, 82 - 145 + 171 - 198. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1096 - 3642.1862. tb 00945. x" type="journal article" year="1862">Walker, 1862</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Singh, N. &amp; Joshi, R. &amp; Kirti, J. S. &amp; Bisht, S. S. &amp; Param, H. S." box="[691,902,331,357]" pageId="4" pageNumber="83" pagination="1" refId="ref10678" refString="Singh, N., Joshi, R., Kirti, J. S., Bisht, S. S. &amp; Param, H. S. (2021 e) A catalogue of Indian Arctiinae (Erebidae, Lepidoptera). Zootaxa, 5058 (1), 001 - 118. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 5058.1.1" type="journal article" year="2021">
Singh 
<emphasis box="[765,822,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="83">et al.</emphasis>
2021e
</bibRefCitation>
). Majority of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Moore" authorityYear="1878" box="[1097,1190,331,357]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Nishada" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="83" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1097,1190,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="83">Nishada</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have unmarked whitish-yellow or beige wings with characteristically elongated forewings and short hindwings. In males, the shortness of the hindwing is more evident where the androconial bearing subcostal area is extended and sometimes folded. The male genitalia generally bear a large spine-like process originating subbasally from the valva costa.
</paragraph>
